      • link

        SinglyLinkedList.Node<E> link(SinglyLinkedList.Node<E> prev,
                              E element,
                              SinglyLinkedList.Node<E> next)
        Creates a new link in the list after prev that should be followed by next. Additionally:
        • If prev == null, then first is changed to reference this new node.
        • If next == null, then last is changed to reference this new node.
        Parameters:
        prev - Node which should precede the new node
        element - Value of the new node
        next - Node which will follow the new node
        Returns:
        The newly created node

      • unlink

        E unlink(SinglyLinkedList.Node<E> node)
        Removes the specified link from the list. If the link immediately preceding this one is known, then unlink(Node, Node) should be used instead, as this case can be optimized for.
        Parameters:
        node - Node to unlink
        Returns:
        Value of the node
        See Also:
        unlink(Node, Node)

      • unlink

        E unlink(SinglyLinkedList.Node<E> prev,
         SinglyLinkedList.Node<E> node)
        Removes the specified link from the list. If prev is not known, then unlink(Node) may be used instead.
        Parameters:
        prev - Node which immediately precedes node
        node - Node to unlink
        Returns:
